        <abstract>
            <p>Extended discussion of their respective difficulties with the definition and status of species and with the extent to which the theory of transmutation may be applied.</p>
            <p>Has rediscovered S. S. Haldeman’s 1844 paper defending the transmutation theory with great skill.</p>
            <p>Asks for reference to Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire’s first enunciation of the progressive development and transmutation theory.</p>
        </abstract>
